{
  "id": "mudanca_base",
  "title": "MudanĂ§a de base do logaritmo",
  "initial": [
    "<strong>Teorema.</strong> \\(\\log_b(x) = \\frac{\\log_a(x)}{\\log_a(b)}\\), com \\(a,b>0\\), \\(a \\neq 1\\), \\(b \\neq 1\\), \\(x>0\\).",
    "<strong>DemonstraĂ§ĂŁo.</strong> Seja \\(\\log_b(x) = y\\).",
    "EntĂŁo \\(b^y = x\\)."
  ],
  "blocks": [
    "Aplicando logaritmo na base \\(a\\): \\(\\log_a(b^y) = \\log_a(x)\\).",
    "Pela propriedade da potĂȘncia: \\(y \\cdot \\log_a(b) = \\log_a(x)\\).",
    "Isolando \\(y\\): \\(y = \\frac{\\log_a(x)}{\\log_a(b)}\\).",
    "Mas \\(y = \\log_b(x)\\).",
    "Substituindo: \\(\\log_b(x) = \\frac{\\log_a(x)}{\\log_a(b)}\\).",
    "Portanto, a mudanĂ§a de base estĂĄ demonstrada."
  ],
  "final": [
    "Logo, \\(\\log_b(x) = \\frac{\\log_a(x)}{\\log_a(b)}\\)."
  ]
},


{
  "id": "bhaskara",
  "title": "FĂłrmula de Bhaskara",
  "initial": [
    "<strong>Teorema.</strong> As soluĂ§Ă”es de \\(ax^2 + bx + c = 0\\), com \\(a \\neq 0\\), sĂŁo \\(x = \\frac{-b \\pm \\sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}\\).",
    "<strong>DemonstraĂ§ĂŁo.</strong> Considere a equaĂ§ĂŁo \\(ax^2 + bx + c = 0\\).",
    "Dividindo por \\(a\\): \\(x^2 + \\frac{b}{a}x + \\frac{c}{a} = 0\\)."
  ],
  "blocks": [
    "Isolando o termo constante: \\(x^2 + \\frac{b}{a}x = -\\frac{c}{a}\\).",
    "Completando o quadrado: somamos \\(\\left(\\frac{b}{2a}\\right)^2\\) aos dois lados.",
    "\\(x^2 + \\frac{b}{a}x + \\left(\\frac{b}{2a}\\right)^2 = -\\frac{c}{a} + \\left(\\frac{b}{2a}\\right)^2\\).",
    "O lado esquerdo torna-se \\(\\left(x + \\frac{b}{2a}\\right)^2\\).",
    "Simplificando o lado direito: \\(\\frac{b^2 - 4ac}{4a^2}\\).",
    "Extraindo a raiz: \\(x + \\frac{b}{2a} = \\pm \\frac{\\sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}\\)."
  ],
  "final": [
    "Isolando \\(x\\), obtemos \\(x = \\frac{-b \\pm \\sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}\\)."
  ]
},


